I asked a similar question in the issues section called "publishing data from a NOMAD-oasis" https://discord.com/channels/[REDACTED_PHONE]/[REDACTED_PHONE] and want to crosslink it here. I work in a project called MaMMoS where we have to share data of magnetic materials from our Oasis to central-NOMAD. We have set up the Oasis and a distro-dev to test code for first parsers (https://github.com/MaMMoS-project/nomad-mammos-plugin). Since we have to publish an initial data set rather soon, until mid-end of June 2025, I need to know if we should continue developing parsers for our simulation and measurement data or should we consider other ways to publish our data/metadata. I am pretty sure that we would need new 'metadata fields' in central NOMAD (hope I use the right terminology here)?

@Guillaume_Gaisné could you already publish some data from your Oasis? Did you use the branch of @Markus_Scheidgen / @Theodore_Chang_DM_BITTE https://gitlab.mpcdf.mpg.de/nomad-lab/nomad-FAIR/-/compare/develop...2117-configuration-and-less-restrictions-on-the-data-transfer? Hi @Wilfried_Hortschitz,

If the data in your Oasis is using custom schemas and parsers, then it is currently not possible to transfer it to our central deployment: we do not yet have robust mechanisms for transferring schemas which would allow the data to be stored in a "read-only" mode in the central service. So for your goals this summer I would look into other solutions. if your Oasis is publicly available, you might be able to publish the data directly there (getting DOI's will require you to connect your Oasis with a DOI service), or then publish the data in some of the other generic data service like Zenodo.
