@Sarthak_Kapoor and I encountered some issue when trying to run a plugin (which was created with the new plugin mechanism from the template showed in last weeks tutorial) locally on a nomad development environment. @Hampus_Näsström helped us figure out what's the problem. More as documentation for others, multiple thing were found: 
- Plugins with the new mechanism don't need to be listed under the `plugins/options` section in the `nomad.yaml`. It seems being `pip install`ed is enough. - On the contrary, to list the plugin there leads to an error: `ValueError: ('The python package nomad_UBIK_plugin cannot be loaded.', AttributeError("'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get_filename'"))`
- Furthermore, the `plugins/include` section of the `nomad.yaml` apparently is an "include only". (I wasn't aware of that tbh!) The only way to get our plugin running was to omit it completely, which includes every available plugin. Then it is correctly shown in the metainfo browser or the about/information page. - We have not found a way yet to use it with the include section.

